Package: crime
Title: A Comprehensive Set of Functions to Clean, Analyze, and Present Crime Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Jacob", "Kaplan", email = "jacobkap@sas.upenn.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A collection of functions that make it easier to understand crime data, and assist others in understanding it. The package helps you read data from various sources, cleans it, fixes column names, and graph or map the data. It can work with various federal and local datasets. 
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    RSocrata,
    jsonlite,
    lubridate,
    ggmap,
    readr,
    tm,
    foreign
License: GPL
LazyData: TRUE
URL: https://github.com/jacobkap/crime
BugReports: https://github.com/jacobkap/crime/issues
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1.9000
